data.enText: the behaviour of a person when they feel that they are more important than other people, so that they are rude to them or do not consider them

simple_means.memory_skill: ar 表加强 + rog 要求 + ance 表状态 → 傲慢

tr: overbearing pride evidenced by a superior manner toward inferiors

value.def: Someone who is arrogant behaves in a proud, unpleasant way towards other people because they believe that they are more important than others.

example.tran: 那话听起来很嚣张，是不是？
自高自大、事不关己的态度

example.ex: At times the arrogance of those in power is quite blatant.
example.tran: 有时那些当权者颇为傲慢嚣张。

example.ex: Later, Simpson arrogantly claimed: 'We won't lose another game.'
example.tran: 稍后，辛普森傲慢地宣称：“我们不会再输了。”

partsOfSpeech.dec: ab 去掉 + rog 要求；问 + ate 做，造成，使… → 去掉要求〔的权利〕→ 取消
ar 表加强 + rog 要求；问 + ance 表状态 → 傲慢
ar 加强 + rog 要求；问 + ant …的 → 无理要求的 → 傲慢的
ar 加强 + rog 要求；问 + ate 做，造成，使… → 一再要求得到 → 霸占
de 向下 + rog 要求；问 + ate 做，造成，使… → 要求低下 → 堕落
de 向下 + rog 要求；问 + atory 有…性质的 → 贬低的
inter 相互 + rog 要求；问 + ate 做，造成，使… → 一问一答 → 审问
pre 预先 + rog 要求；问 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 可预先要求 → 特权
rog 要求；问 + ue → 提出过分要求的人 → 无赖
